[style name="res://Dialogue/Styles/CozyPersonaVN.tres"]
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
The morning sun shines over the quiet neighborhood.
A sedan is parked neatly outside the Ilagan house.
The street is calm. A few neighbors sweep their front yards while children walk toward school.
The front gate slowly opens.
Ethan walks toward the house carrying a small paper bag from a local bakery.
He pauses for a moment before ringing the doorbell.
DING DONG.
[signal arg="sfx:doorbell"]
A few seconds pass.
The door opens.
Ricardo stands at the doorway.
His expression immediately softens.
Ethan. Maaga ka ah.
Chuckling.
May dala po akong pandesal.
Fresh pa.
Ricardo smiles.
Aba... Sakto.
Kape na lang kulang.
Pasok ka na, hijo.
Ethan steps inside.
The house feels unusually quiet.
The television is off.
No music plays.
The silence feels heavier than usual.
Ethan notices Jennifer arranging a few things on a nearby shelf.
Ethan notices Jennifer standing near the living room.
She's looking down at her phone.
Her thumb scrolls absentmindedly through social media.
Good morning po, Tita.
Jennifer doesn't respond immediately.
Still focused on her screen.
A beat passes.
She suddenly looks up.
Ay...
Good morning, Ethan.
Pasensya na.
Ethan smiles politely.
Okay lang po.
He hands her the paper bag.
May pandesal po.
Naku.
Hindi na sana nag-abala.
Okay lang po.
Napadaan lang.
Jennifer smiles politely.
But her eyes betray her exhaustion.
She hasn't been sleeping well.
Ethan notices.
He doesn't mention it.
Instead...
Nasaan po si Maya?
Jennifer pauses.
She glances toward the hallway.
Nasa kwarto pa nya..
Ethan nods.
The answer is enough.
Ricardo walks toward the kitchen.
Kape muna tayo.
Baka magising din 'yon si Maya.
The aroma of freshly brewed coffee fills the room.
The paper bag of pandesal sits in the middle of the table.
Jennifer begins serving everyone.
The atmosphere is noticeably lighter than it has been in days.
Buti napadaan ka, Ethan.
Hindi ka na masyadong nakakabisita rito.
Medyo naging busy lang po.
Thesis.
Requirements.
Alam n'yo naman.
Ricardo nods absentmindedly.
His phone vibrates beside his coffee.
[signal arg="sfx:phone_notif"]
[signal arg="emotion_persist:nervous:2"]
He glances at the screen.
A customer asking for an update on a repair.
Without thinking...
He begins typing a reply.
Raising an eyebrow.
Hon...
Mamaya na 'yan.
Kumakain tayo.
Ricardo looks up.
As if only now realizing what he was doing.
Ah. Sorry.
He locks his phone and sets it beside his plate.
Smiles.
Okay lang po, Tito.
Work is work.
Chuckles sheepishly.
Sensya na, minsan...nadadala lang talaga.
Normal lang 'yan.
Last stretch na.
Konting tiis na lang.
Ethan nods.
Jennifer smiles proudly.
She glances toward Maya's empty seat.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:lost:2"]
Gano'n din si Maya.
Halos hindi na nga lumalabas ng kwarto kakaaral.
Kung minsan kailangan ko pang pilitin magpahinga.
Ricardo smiles.
Mana sa sipag.
Jennifer chuckles.
Kaya nga kahit nahihirapan...
Alam kong kakayanin niya.
Hindi naman basta sumusuko ang anak namin.
Ethan smiles politely.
He hesitates.
Unsure whether to say anything.
Then...
Actually po... Okay na ba siya?
The room grows quieter.
Jennifer looks at him. Confused.
Anong ibig mong sabihin?
Ethan blinks.
He immediately realizes something is off.
Ah...
Akala ko po... Nasabi na niya.
Jennifer slowly lowers her spoon.
Nasabi ang alin?
Ethan looks between Jennifer and Ricardo.
Then toward the hallway.
His expression changes.
He wasn't supposed to be the one saying it.
He remembers the message Maya sent him weeks ago, venting about the failed requirement.
He assumed that if she told him, she'd told them too.
He never considered that texting him had been the safer version of the truth.
...
About po doon sa...major requirement niya.
Silence.
Ricardo frowns.
Anong requirement?
Ethan swallows.
His voice becomes quieter.
Yung... Hindi niya po naipasa.
The room falls completely silent.
Jennifer stares at him.
As if she misheard.
...
Ano?
Ethan quickly shakes his head.
Tita... Akala ko talaga alam n'yo na.
I'm sorry.
Jennifer slowly stands.
Her eyes remain fixed on Ethan.
Hindi niya sinabi sa'min.
Ricardo's expression hardens.
He looks toward the hallway leading to Maya's room.
A mixture of confusion...
And disappointment.
Kailan pa nangyari 'to?
Ethan rubs the back of his neck.
Clearly uncomfortable.
Matagal na po.
I... I thought napag-usapan niyo na.
Nobody responds.
The silence becomes unbearable.
Jennifer slowly exhales.
Trying to process everything.
So...
Habang sinasabi niyang okay lang siya... Habang sinasabi niyang kaya niya...
Hindi pala totoo.
Ricardo doesn't answer.
His jaw tightens.
For the first time...
Neither parent knows what to believe anymore.
Ethan looks toward Maya's closed bedroom door.
Guilt washes over him.
He never intended to expose her.
He simply assumed...
Her parents already knew.
Instead...
He had revealed the truth himself.
And in doing so...
The trust inside the Ilagan household quietly began to crumble.
The dining table remains untouched.
The cups of coffee have gone cold.
Ricardo sits at the head of the table.
Jennifer quietly folds a dish towel in her hands, more out of nervousness than necessity.
Ethan sits across from them.
No one says a word.
Ricardo breaks the silence.
Hindi puwedeng ganito na lang, Jen.
Jennifer looks up and sighs.
Alam ko pero-.
Pause.
-pero hindi ko alam kung paano magsisimula.
Ricardo nods in agreement.
Ethan looks toward the hallway.
Maybe...
Hindi niyo kailangang alam agad ang tamang sasabihin.
Baka...
kailangan lang muna niyang maramdaman na gusto niyo siyang pakinggan.
Jennifer slowly lowers her eyes.
She quietly nods.
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/mayas_room.png" fade="0.7"]
A soft knock is heard.
Anak...
Pwede ba tayong mag-usap?
Maya looks up from her phone and towards the door.
She takes a deep breath.
[signal arg="sfx:breath_shaky"]
Her phone screen glowing in her hands she lets out a dull sigh.
... Sige po.
Ricardo opens the door slowly.
Jennifer stands beside him.
Her posture is rigid, arms tightly crossed.
She looks frustrated, her eyes scanning the room suspiciously .
Ethan quietly stays behind in the hallway, looking down awkwardly.
Ricardo gestures toward the living room.
Labas muna tayo sa sala .
Kailangan natin mag-usap ng matino .
Ayoko ng pabalang na sagot, Maya ha.
Maya stares at her phone for a brief second before locking it.
She quietly stands and walks past them.
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
The three sit facing each other.
Ricardo takes the single armchair, immediately rubbing his temples
Maya and Jennifer sit on opposite ends of the sofa.
Maya immediately places her phone face up on her lap.
The distance between them feels like a literal wall. .
Nobody speaks.
Until...
Anak...
Hindi pwedeng ganiyan ang ugali mo sa amin kagabi... Nagtatanong lang naman kami tungkol sa mga klase mo,diba?
Maya looks away, her finger tapping the side of her phone.
Sumagot naman po ako, 'di ba?
Sagot ba 'yung puro 'okay lang' habang nakatutok ka dyan sa selpone mo? Maya,'yung scholarship mo hindi yan basta basta lang!
Maya sighs dramatically. She unlocks her phone right in front of them.
[signal arg="sfx:phone_lock"]
Ma, malaking part ng buhay ko 'toh. Hindi ko pwedeng itigil lang 'to para sa mga requirements na 'yan.
Jennifer gets defensive, sitting up straight.
Maya, drawing lng yan sa cellphone mo! Ano gagawin mo sa drawing kung hindi mo naman matatapos yung kurso mo? Tingnan mo nga si Ethan!
Maya flinches at the name. She locks her eyes onto her screen.
Si Ethan, sobrang responsable. Nakakatulong na nga kay Papa mo sa shop, maayos pa sa school, walang tinatago sa pamilya niya. Siya, may direksyon sa buhay. Ikaw, ano?
Jennifer looks at Maya intensely
[signal arg="emotion_persist:nervous:2"]
Maya's fingers anxiously scroll through her device, ignoring her mother's gaze.
Kung gustong-gusto niyo pala 'yung mga choices ni Ethan sa buhay, di sana siya na lang ang naging anak niyo.
Ricardo sits up and points a finger towards Maya
Maya! Huwag mong bastusin ang nanay mo ng ganyan!
Bakit, Pa? Totoo naman di ba? Tuwang-tuwa kayo kapag si Ethan ang kasama mo sa shop. Lagi mo siyang pinupuri habang ako, kahit anong pilit kong maging Dean's Lister, lagi nalang kulang sa inyo.
The comparison stings, pushing Maya further into her shell.
She stares at her screen, watching chat bubbles pop up from her thesis mates.
Palagi niyo na lang akong ikinukumpara sa iba. Pero nakikita niyo ba kung gaano ako nahihirapan sa course na to? I just feel like you guys don't understand or see me at all eh. And yung nakikita niyo lang, ah yung mga bagsak kong requirements.
Ricardo opens his mouth to speak, but his phone suddenly vibrates loudly on the table.
An automated work alert flashes on his screen.
)
Ricardo opens his mouth to respond, but his phone suddenly vibrates loudly on the table.
An automated work alert flashes across the screen.)
Almost instinctively, Ricardo reaches for it.
His eyes leave Maya for only a few seconds.
But to Maya...
It feels much longer.
She lets out a quiet, bitter laugh.
...
Kita n'yo?
Pause.
Kahit ngayon...
Hindi niyo man lang ako matapos pakinggan.
Ricardo freezes.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:nervous:2"]
His hand remains on the phone.
Laging may mas importante.
Trabaho.
Grades.
Kung ano'ng iniisip ng ibang tao.
Pause.
Ako...
Parang laging pangalawa.
Ricardo slowly lowers his phone.
He wants to explain himself...
But no words come out.
See? Kahit ngayon... mas importante pa rin 'yan sa inyo.
Ricardo quickly puts his phone away, looking guilty but exhausted.
Sinusubukan ko lang kumita sa buhay, Maya... Para rin sa iyo ang lahat ng pinaghirapan ko. Sayang lang ang ginagawa ko kung sinusuportahan ko ang pag-aaral mo tapos puro ka lang doodle araw-araw.
Maya turns her back slightly, completely tuning out their words with her phone.
Gagawan ko naman ng paraan yung mga grades ko Pa. Please..wag niyo na lang muna akong kausapin tungkol dito.
Jennifer snaps, losing her patience.
[signal arg="drain:on"]
[signal arg="emotion_persist:angry:2"]
Ricardo stares and tries to process what his daughter said.
Maya, tabi mo nga muna 'yung selpone mo kapag kinakausap kita!
Maya grips her phone tighter as her ultimate shield.
Her mind is a chaotic mess of assignment alerts, but she stays completely numb.
Ayoko po. Di ko po kaya.
The room falls into a freezing silence.
No one rushes to bridge the gap. No one apologizes. They are physically together, but entirely separated by their screens and pride.
Ricardo lets out a heavy, tired sigh.
Sige. Bahala ka sa buhay mo kung yan ang gusto mo edi sige. Basta bantayan mo 'yang mga grades mo, ha.
Maya doesn't answer. She stands up and quietly walks back to her room.
Jennifer and Ricardo are left sitting on the sofa in deep, unresolved disappointment.
Months later.
The family sits around in the living room once again.
The golden light of sunset shines through the windows, but the room feels cold.
The atmosphere is quiet, but unlike before, it is not a peaceful silence. It is an awkward, fragile truce.
Maya finally looks up from her phone.
She notices her father situated beside her, typing away.
Her mother sat nearby as well, watching something on her tablet.
Despite their closeness, Maya still feels lonely.
"Ganito nalang ba kami?"
Maya sinks further into the couch.
She succumbs to her train of thought, shifting to a more comfortable position.
"Ganito nalang ba... ako?"
Her eyes droop a little, and she tries not to nod off.
"Maybe it's alright..."
"That I don't know yet."
A little while later.
Maya feels something warm, and begins to stir.
She must have fallen asleep, phone still in her hand, but with her arm now over a warm blanket.
She blinks, adjusting to the dimming light.
She notices Jennifer walking back toward the kitchen, her hands empty.
[signal arg="emotion_persist:lost:2"]
Her mother was the one who put the blanket on her, but neither of them says a word about it.
Ricardo is typing away on his phone, answering a shop customer.
Jennifer is scrolling through her tablet, checking social media.
Maya is quietly sitting on the other end of the couch, watching them. The distance between them feels physical, yet there's a small change.
Jennifer stops scrolling for a moment. She glances at Maya.
Maya... yung tungkol sa balak mong pag-shift.
Maya pulls her eyes away from her phone, looking up.
May... may final na desisyon ka na ba kung anong lilipatan mo?
Maya hesitates, her fingers lightly tapping the back of her phone case.
Instead of getting defensive like before, she takes a quiet, calm breath.
Honestly, Ma... hindi ko pa po alam kung anong exact course.
Pause.
Pero inaayos ko pa po yung mga basic requirements habang nag-iisip. Pero... okay lang naman po siguro yon, di ba? Na hindi ko pa alam agad.
Jennifer looks at her tablet, then back to Maya. She lets out a small, tired sigh.
Matatakot pa rin naman ako para sa future mo Maya. Hindi naman nawawala yon sa magulang.
Pause.
Pero... sige. Kung kailangan mo ng oras para hanapin yung totoong gusto mo, hindi na muna kita mamadaliin.
Maya blinks, slightly caught off guard. She feels a tiny weight leave her shoulders.
Salamat po, Ma.
Ricardo lowers his phone to his lap, looking over at both of them.
Basta huwag mo lang pababayaan yung natitirang subjects mo ngayon, ha. Ayusin mo pa rin habang naghahanap ka ng gagawin mo sa buhay mo sabihan mo lang kami kung may kailangan ka.
Opo, Pa. Gagawan ko po ng paraan.
Maya nods silently
The family moves toward the dining table as evening begins to set in.
Ricardo continues typing on his phone while walking, answering one last work thread.
Jennifer walks beside him, scrolling through a notification on her device.
They sit down, and the family shares the same space. Conversations remain brief and somewhat awkward, but the biting tension from before is gone.
Without looking up from her screen
Kumain na kayo. Lumalamig 'yung ulam.
Answering a text
Oo, sandali lang. May tinatapos lang sa chat.
Maya watches them. She takes her own phone and places it face up on the table right next to her plate.
Jennifer places her face up as well. Then Ricardo.
Three screens glow quietly in the dimming room, occasionally lighting up with notifications.
They are still heavily attached to their devices. They still look down more than they look up. But as Maya picks up her utensils, she notices small, subtle shifts. Jennifer's scrolling is less frantic. Ricardo is staying at the table instead of running off to the shop.
Maya watches them for a moment.
She hesitates.
She speaks softly.
Pwede bang...
Kahit habang kumakain lang...
Bawas muna tayo sa phone?
Jennifer and Ricardo both look up.
A brief silence.
They glance at each other.
Without a word...
Jennifer slowly places her phone beside her plate.
Ricardo finishes typing one last message.
Then sets his phone down as well.
Three screens glow quietly in the dimming room.
Notifications continue to appear.
None of them reaches for their phone.
They begin eating.
The conversation is still sparse.
Still awkward.
But this time...
They occasionally look up.
Meeting each other's eyes.
Listening.
Even if only for a moment.
[signal arg="drain:off"]
Some things have remained the same, and the emotional distance hasn't magically disappeared. But the wounds are slowly starting to scar over.
Maya looks out the window at the darkening sky, then down at her phone.
She leaves the house tomorrow still feeling uncertain about her future requirements.
But looking at the quiet table, she feels a strange, small spark of hope.
She doesn't have the roadmap yet but she's willing to keep searching for her own answers.
The three of them continue eating in their quiet, routine bubble, screens glowing softly against their faces. The old family photo lingers even more.
The space is unchanged.
No new art is up yet.
But the air feels just a little lighter.
THE END.

jump act_ending/
